text.__SUMMARY__: Eucalyptus spreta is a mallee tree that is native to an area on the southern coast of Western Australia.The mallee tree typically grows to a height of 4 to 10 metres (13 to 33 ft) and has smooth bark. The adult leaves are green and have a disjunct arrangement. The flowers are white or cream with a calyx calyptrate and shed early. Fruit are linear and cuboid and contain red seeds.It grows in flat areas with calcareous loam or red sand soil types.
text.Distribution: Eucalyptus spreta is found in the IBRA Regions of Coolgardie, Mallee, Nullarbor, and  in the Local Government Areas of Dundas and Esperance.
